SIMPLE: malvaceous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malvaceous
<hw>Mal*va"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>malvaceus</ets>, from <ets>malva</ets> mallows. See
<er>Mallow</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
resembling, a natural family of plants (<fam>Malvaceae</fam>), of which
the mallow is the type. The cotton plant, hollyhock, and abutilon are of
this family. It was formerly classified as an order, and included the
baobab and the silk-cotton trees. The baobab and silk-cotton trees are
now placed in the family <fam>Bombacaceae</fam>, which is included with
the <fam>Malvaceae</fam> in the order <ord>Malvales</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malvales</ent>⟦br⟧
